WEEK 1 – Data Cleaning & Setup Report
Objective

The primary goal of Week 1 was to prepare the dataset for analysis by performing essential data cleaning and setup tasks using Excel.

Tasks Performed

1. Load Data in Excel

Imported the dataset into Excel
Verified that all data was properly loaded into the worksheet

2. Check Dataset Information

Reviewed columns, data types, and overall structure
Used filters and basic Excel tools to understand data distribution

3. Handle Missing Values

Identified blank cells in the dataset
Filled missing values or removed rows where necessary

4. Remove Duplicates

Used “Remove Duplicates” feature in Excel
Ensured data consistency by eliminating repeated records

5. Standardize Dates

Formatted date columns into a consistent date format
Ensured uniformity for accurate analysis

6. Save Cleaned Dataset

Saved the cleaned dataset in Excel/CSV format
Ensured the file is ready for further analysis

7. Upload Work to GitHub

Created/used a GitHub repository
Uploaded the cleaned dataset file
Organized files with proper naming and structure
